me1200QosMIB.name: me1200QosMIB

Do no use Unsigned32 for indexes

me1200QosMIB.description: This is a private MIB for QoS

ME1200DestMacType.name: ME1200DestMacType
ME1200DestMacType.description: Represents a destination MAC type selector.

ME1200DscpClassify.name: ME1200DscpClassify
ME1200DscpClassify.description: An integer that indicates the DSCP classify mode.

ME1200DscpRemark.name: ME1200DscpRemark
ME1200DscpRemark.description: An integer that indicates the DSCP remark mode.

ME1200MaxSelector.name: ME1200MaxSelector
ME1200MaxSelector.description: An integer that selects between 'Maximum Drop Probability' or 'Maximum Fill Level'.

ME1200QceFrameType.name: ME1200QceFrameType
ME1200QceFrameType.description: An integer that indicates the QCE frame type key.

ME1200QceUserType.name: ME1200QceUserType
ME1200QceUserType.description: An integer that indicates the QCE user type. If the value is zero it indicates a static configuration. If the value is non-zero it indicates a dynamic configuration made by another subsystem.

ME1200TagRemarkingMode.name: ME1200TagRemarkingMode
ME1200TagRemarkingMode.description: An integer that indicates the tag remarking mode.

ME1200VcapKeyType.name: ME1200VcapKeyType
ME1200VcapKeyType.description: Represents a VCAP key type selector.

ME1200VlanTagType.name: ME1200VlanTagType
ME1200VlanTagType.description: Represents a VLAN tag type selector.

me1200QosStormPolicerUnicastEnable.name: me1200QosStormPolicerUnicastEnable
me1200QosStormPolicerUnicastEnable.description: If true, the storm policer is enabled.

me1200QosStormPolicerMulticastEnable.name: me1200QosStormPolicerMulticastEnable
me1200QosStormPolicerMulticastEnable.description: If true, the storm policer is enabled.

me1200QosStormPolicerBroadcastEnable.name: me1200QosStormPolicerBroadcastEnable
me1200QosStormPolicerBroadcastEnable.description: If true, the storm policer is enabled.

me1200QosWredTable.name: me1200QosWredTable
me1200QosWredTable.description: This table contains the configuration of WRED for queue 0 through 5

me1200QosWredEntry.name: me1200QosWredEntry
me1200QosWredEntry.description: Each row contains the configuration for a specific queue

me1200QosWredEnable.name: me1200QosWredEnable
me1200QosWredEnable.description: If true, RED is enabled for this queue

me1200QosWredMinimumFillLevel.name: me1200QosWredMinimumFillLevel
me1200QosWredMinimumFillLevel.description: Controls the lower RED fill level threshold in percent of the whole queue. If the queue filling level is below this threshold, the drop probability is zero. Valid range is 0-100

me1200QosWredMaximum.name: me1200QosWredMaximum
me1200QosWredMaximum.description: Controls the upper RED drop probability or fill level threshold for frames marked with Drop Precedence Level 1 (yellow frames). Valid range is 1-100

me1200QosWredMaxSelector.name: me1200QosWredMaxSelector
me1200QosWredMaxSelector.description: Selects whether 'Maximum' controls 'Maximum Drop Probability' or 'Maximum Fill Level'.

me1200QosDscpTable.name: me1200QosDscpTable
me1200QosDscpTable.description: This table has 64 entries, one for each DSCP value

me1200QosDscpEntry.name: me1200QosDscpEntry
me1200QosDscpEntry.description: Each row contains the configuration for a specific DSCP

me1200QosDscpTrust.name: me1200QosDscpTrust
me1200QosDscpTrust.description: If true, this DSCP value is trusted. Packets arriving on interfaces where 'TrustDscp' is enabled will be classified to the corresponding CoS and DPL in this table.

me1200QosDscpCos.name: me1200QosDscpCos
me1200QosDscpCos.description: The CoS value which the DSCP value maps to. Valid range is 0-7.

me1200QosDscpDpl.name: me1200QosDscpDpl
me1200QosDscpDpl.description: The DPL (Drop Precedence Level) which the DSCP value maps to. Valid range is 0-1.

me1200QosDscpIngressTranslation.name: me1200QosDscpIngressTranslation
me1200QosDscpIngressTranslation.description: The new classified DSCP value which the original DSCP value is replaced with if 'DscpTranslate' is enabled on the interface

me1200QosDscpClassify.name: me1200QosDscpClassify
me1200QosDscpClassify.description: If true, then packets received on interfaces where 'DscpClassify' is set to 'selected' will be classified to a new DSCP value based on the classified CoS and DPL value configured in the qosCosDscpTable.

me1200QosDscpEgressTranslation.name: me1200QosDscpEgressTranslation
me1200QosDscpEgressTranslation.description: The new DSCP value that will be written into the packet at egress if 'DscpRemark' on the interface is set to 'remap' or 'remap-dp'. If 'remap-dp' is set then only packets classified to Dpl 0 will use this table.

me1200QosDscpEgressTranslationDp1.name: me1200QosDscpEgressTranslationDp1
me1200QosDscpEgressTranslationDp1.description: The new DSCP value that will be written into the packet at egress if 'DscpRemark' on the interface is set to 'remap-dp'. Only packets classified to Dpl 1 will use this table.

me1200QosCosToDscpTable.name: me1200QosCosToDscpTable
me1200QosCosToDscpTable.description: This table has QOS_CLASS_CNT entries, one for each Cos value

me1200QosCosToDscpEntry.name: me1200QosCosToDscpEntry
me1200QosCosToDscpEntry.description: Each row contains the configuration for a specific Cos

me1200QosCosToDscpDscp.name: me1200QosCosToDscpDscp
me1200QosCosToDscpDscp.description: The DSCP value which the classified CoS value maps to when the classified DPL is 0.

me1200QosCosToDscpDscpDp1.name: me1200QosCosToDscpDscpDp1
me1200QosCosToDscpDscpDp1.description: The DSCP value which the classified CoS value maps to when the classified DPL is 1.

me1200QosQceTable.name: me1200QosQceTable
me1200QosQceTable.description: This table contains the configuration of QCEs. The index is QceId.

me1200QosQceEntry.name: me1200QosQceEntry
me1200QosQceEntry.description: Each row contains the configuration of a single QCE.

me1200QosQceNextQceId.name: me1200QosQceNextQceId
me1200QosQceNextQceId.description: QCE Id of the next QCE.

me1200QosQcePortList.name: me1200QosQcePortList
me1200QosQcePortList.description: List of ports that are member of this QCE.

me1200QosQceDestMacType.name: me1200QosQceDestMacType
me1200QosQceDestMacType.description: Indicates the destination MAC type to match.

me1200QosQceDestMac.name: me1200QosQceDestMac
me1200QosQceDestMac.description: Indicates the 48 bits destination MAC address. The packets destination address is AND-ed with the value of DestMacMask and then compared against the value of this object. If this object value and the value of DestMacMask is 00-00-00-00-00-00, this entry matches any destination MAC address. This object can only be configured if DestMacType is any(0) and DestMacMask is ff-ff-ff-ff-ff-ff.

me1200QosQceDestMacMask.name: me1200QosQceDestMacMask
me1200QosQceDestMacMask.description: Indicates the 48 bits destination MAC address mask.Valid values are 00-00-00-00-00-00 or ff-ff-ff-ff-ff-ff.

me1200QosQceSrcMac.name: me1200QosQceSrcMac
me1200QosQceSrcMac.description: Indicates the 48 bits source MAC address. The packets source address is AND-ed with the value of SrcMacMask and then compared against the value of this object. If this object value and the value of SrcMacMask is 00-00-00-00-00-00, this entry matches any source MAC address. This object can only be configured if SrcMacMask is ff-ff-ff-ff-ff-ff.

me1200QosQceSrcMacMask.name: me1200QosQceSrcMacMask
me1200QosQceSrcMacMask.description: Indicates the 48 bits source MAC address mask. Valid values are 00-00-00-00-00-00 or ff-ff-ff-ff-ff-ff.

me1200QosQceVlanTagType.name: me1200QosQceVlanTagType
me1200QosQceVlanTagType.description: Indicates the VLAN tag type to match.

me1200QosQceVlanIdOp.name: me1200QosQceVlanIdOp
me1200QosQceVlanIdOp.description: Indicates how a packets's VLAN ID is to be compared.

me1200QosQceVlanId.name: me1200QosQceVlanId
me1200QosQceVlanId.description: The VLAN ID to be compared. If the VlanIdOp object in the same row is range(2), this object will be the starting VLAN ID of the range. Valid range is 1-4095. This object can only be configured if VlanIdOp is not any(0).

me1200QosQceVlanIdRange.name: me1200QosQceVlanIdRange
me1200QosQceVlanIdRange.description: The VLAN ID to be compared. If the VlanIdOp object in the same row is range(2), this object will be the ending VLAN ID of the range. Valid range is 1-4095. This object can only be configured if VlanIdOp is range(2).

me1200QosQcePcp.name: me1200QosQcePcp
me1200QosQcePcp.description: The PCP value(s) to be compared.

me1200QosQceDei.name: me1200QosQceDei
me1200QosQceDei.description: The DEI value to be compared. Valid range is 0-1.

me1200QosQceInnerVlanTagType.name: me1200QosQceInnerVlanTagType
me1200QosQceInnerVlanTagType.description: Indicates the inner VLAN tag type to match.

me1200QosQceInnerVlanIdOp.name: me1200QosQceInnerVlanIdOp
me1200QosQceInnerVlanIdOp.description: Indicates how a packets's inner VLAN ID is to be compared.

me1200QosQceInnerVlanId.name: me1200QosQceInnerVlanId
me1200QosQceInnerVlanId.description: The inner VLAN ID to be compared. If the InnerVlanIdOp object in the same row is range(2), this object will be the starting VLAN ID of the range. Valid range is 1-4095. This object can only be configured if InnerVlanIdOp is not any(0).

me1200QosQceInnerVlanIdRange.name: me1200QosQceInnerVlanIdRange
me1200QosQceInnerVlanIdRange.description: The inner VLAN ID to be compared. If the InnerVlanIdOp object in the same row is range(2), this object will be the ending VLAN ID of the range. Valid range is 1-4095. This object can only be configured if InnerVlanIdOp is range(2).

me1200QosQceInnerPcp.name: me1200QosQceInnerPcp
me1200QosQceInnerPcp.description: The inner PCP value(s) to be compared.

me1200QosQceInnerDei.name: me1200QosQceInnerDei
me1200QosQceInnerDei.description: The inner DEI value to be compared. Valid range is 0-1.

me1200QosQceFrameType.name: me1200QosQceFrameType
me1200QosQceFrameType.description: Indicates the packet's frame type. Modifying the frame type on an existing QCE will restore the content of all frame type dependent configuration to default.

me1200QosQceEtype.name: me1200QosQceEtype
me1200QosQceEtype.description: Indicates the packet's 16 bit Ethernet type field. Valid values are: 0(match any), 0x600-0xFFFF but excluding 0x800(IPv4) and 0x86DD(IPv6).This object can only be configured if FrameType is etype(1).

me1200QosQceLlcDsap.name: me1200QosQceLlcDsap
me1200QosQceLlcDsap.description: Indicates the packets's 8 bit LLC DSAP field. The packets LLC DSAP field is AND-ed with the value of LlcDsapMask and then compared against the value of this object. If this object value and the value of LlcDsapMask is 0x00, this entry matches any LLC DSAP. Valid range is 0x00-0xFF. This object can only be configured if FrameType is llc(2).

me1200QosQceLlcDsapMask.name: me1200QosQceLlcDsapMask
me1200QosQceLlcDsapMask.description: Indicates the 8 bit LLC DSAP mask. Valid values are 0x00 or 0xFF. This object can only be configured if FrameType is llc(2).

me1200QosQceLlcSsap.name: me1200QosQceLlcSsap
me1200QosQceLlcSsap.description: Indicates the packets's 8 bit LLC SSAP field. The packets LLC SSAP field is AND-ed with the value of LlcSsapMask and then compared against the value of this object. If this object value and the value of LlcSsapMask is 0x00, this entry matches any LLC SSAP. Valid range is 0x00-0xFF. This object can only be configured if FrameType is llc(2).

me1200QosQceLlcSsapMask.name: me1200QosQceLlcSsapMask
me1200QosQceLlcSsapMask.description: Indicates the 8 bit LLC SSAP mask. Valid values are 0x00 or 0xFF. This object can only be configured if FrameType is llc(2).

me1200QosQceLlcControl.name: me1200QosQceLlcControl
me1200QosQceLlcControl.description: Indicates the packets's 8 bit LLC Control field. The packets LLC Control field is AND-ed with the value of LlcControlMask and then compared against the value of this object. If this object value and the value of LlcControlMask is 0x00, this entry matches any LLC Control. Valid range is 0x00-0xFF. This object can only be configured if FrameType is llc(2).

me1200QosQceLlcControlMask.name: me1200QosQceLlcControlMask
me1200QosQceLlcControlMask.description: Indicates the 8 bit LLC Control mask. Valid values are 0x00 or 0xFF. This object can only be configured if FrameType is llc(2).

me1200QosQceSnapPid.name: me1200QosQceSnapPid
me1200QosQceSnapPid.description: Indicates the packet's 16 bit SNAP PID field. The packets SNAP PID field is AND-ed with the value of SnapPidMask and then compared against the value of this object. If this object value and the value of SnapPidMask is 0x0000, this entry matches any ethertype. This object can only be configured if FrameType is snap(3).

me1200QosQceSnapPidMask.name: me1200QosQceSnapPidMask
me1200QosQceSnapPidMask.description: Indicates the 16 bit SNAP PID mask. Valid values are 0x0000 or 0xFFFF. This object can only be configured if FrameType is snap(3).

me1200QosQceIpv4Fragment.name: me1200QosQceIpv4Fragment
me1200QosQceIpv4Fragment.description: Indicates how an IPv4 fragment bit is to be compared. This object can only be configured if FrameType is ipv4(4).

me1200QosQceIpv4DscpOp.name: me1200QosQceIpv4DscpOp
me1200QosQceIpv4DscpOp.description: Indicates how an IPv4 DSCP field is to be compared. This object can only be configured if FrameType is ipv4(4).

me1200QosQceIpv4Dscp.name: me1200QosQceIpv4Dscp
me1200QosQceIpv4Dscp.description: The DSCP value to be compared. If the Ipv4DscpOp object in the same row is range(2), this object will be the starting DSCP value of the range. Valid range is 0-63. This object can only be configured if FrameType is ipv4(4) and Ipv4DscpOp is not any(0).

me1200QosQceIpv4DscpRange.name: me1200QosQceIpv4DscpRange
me1200QosQceIpv4DscpRange.description: The DSCP value to be compared. If the Ipv4DscpOp object in the same row is range(2), this object will be the ending DSCP value of the range. Valid range is 0-63. This object can only be configured if FrameType is ipv4(4) and Ipv4DscpOp is range(2).

me1200QosQceIpv4Protocol.name: me1200QosQceIpv4Protocol
me1200QosQceIpv4Protocol.description: The protocol number field in the IPv4 header used to indicate a higher layer protocol. The packets protocol number field is AND-ed with the value of Ipv4ProtocolMask and then compared with the value of this object. If Ipv4Protocol and Ipv4protocolMask are 0, this entry matches any IPv4 protocol. Valid range is 0-255. This object can only be configured if FrameType is ipv4(4).

me1200QosQceIpv4ProtocolMask.name: me1200QosQceIpv4ProtocolMask
me1200QosQceIpv4ProtocolMask.description: The specified IPv4 protocol number mask. Valid values are 0 or 255. This object can only be configured if FrameType is ipv4(4).

me1200QosQceIpv4SrcIp.name: me1200QosQceIpv4SrcIp
me1200QosQceIpv4SrcIp.description: The specified IPv4 source address. The packets source address is AND-ed with the value of Ipv4SrcIpMask and then compared with the value of this object. If Ipv4SrcIP and Ipv4SrcIpMask are 0.0.0.0, this entry matches any IPv4 source address. This object can only be configured if FrameType is ipv4(4).

me1200QosQceIpv4SrcIpMask.name: me1200QosQceIpv4SrcIpMask
me1200QosQceIpv4SrcIpMask.description: The specified IPv4 source address mask. This object can only be configured if FrameType is ipv4(4).

me1200QosQceIpv4DestIp.name: me1200QosQceIpv4DestIp
me1200QosQceIpv4DestIp.description: The specified IPv4 destination address. The packets destination address is AND-ed with the value of Ipv4DestIpMask and then compared with the value of this object. If Ipv4DestIP and Ipv4DestIpMask are 0.0.0.0, this entry matches any IPv4 destination address. This object can only be configured if FrameType is ipv4(4).

me1200QosQceIpv4DestIpMask.name: me1200QosQceIpv4DestIpMask
me1200QosQceIpv4DestIpMask.description: The specified IPv4 destination address mask. This object can only be configured if FrameType is ipv4(4).

me1200QosQceIpv4SrcPortOp.name: me1200QosQceIpv4SrcPortOp
me1200QosQceIpv4SrcPortOp.description: Indicates how a packet's source TCP/UDP port number is to be compared. This object can only be configured if FrameType is ipv4(4).

me1200QosQceIpv4SrcPort.name: me1200QosQceIpv4SrcPort
me1200QosQceIpv4SrcPort.description: The source port number of the TCP or UDP protocol. If the Ipv4SrcPortOp object in the same row is range(2), this object will be the starting port number of the port range. Valid range is 0-65535. This object can only be configured if FrameType is ipv4(4) and Ipv4SrcPortOp is not any(0).

me1200QosQceIpv4SrcPortRange.name: me1200QosQceIpv4SrcPortRange
me1200QosQceIpv4SrcPortRange.description: The source port number of the TCP or UDP protocol. If the Ipv4SrcPortOp object in the same row is range(2), this object will be the ending port number of the port range. Valid range is 0-65535. This object can only be configured if FrameType is ipv4(4) and Ipv4SrcPortOp is range(2).

me1200QosQceIpv4DestPortOp.name: me1200QosQceIpv4DestPortOp
me1200QosQceIpv4DestPortOp.description: Indicates how a packet's destination TCP/UDP port number is to be compared. This object can only be configured if FrameType is ipv4(4).

me1200QosQceIpv4DestPort.name: me1200QosQceIpv4DestPort
me1200QosQceIpv4DestPort.description: The destination port number of the TCP or UDP protocol. If the Ipv4DestPortOp object in the same row is range(2), this object will be the starting port number of the port range. Valid range is 0-65535. This object can only be configured if FrameType is ipv4(4) and Ipv4DestPortOp is not any(0).

me1200QosQceIpv4DestPortRange.name: me1200QosQceIpv4DestPortRange
me1200QosQceIpv4DestPortRange.description: The source port number of the TCP or UDP protocol. If the Ipv4DestPortOp object in the same row is range(2), this object will be the ending port number of the port range. Valid range is 0-65535. This object can only be configured if FrameType is ipv4(4) and Ipv4DestPortOp is range(2).

me1200QosQceIpv6DscpOp.name: me1200QosQceIpv6DscpOp
me1200QosQceIpv6DscpOp.description: Indicates how an IPv6 DSCP field is to be compared. This object can only be configured if FrameType is ipv6(5).

me1200QosQceIpv6Dscp.name: me1200QosQceIpv6Dscp
me1200QosQceIpv6Dscp.description: The DSCP value to be compared. If the Ipv6DscpOp object in the same row is range(2), this object will be the starting DSCP value of the range. Valid range is 0-63. This object can only be configured if FrameType is ipv6(5) and Ipv6DscpOp is not any(0).

me1200QosQceIpv6DscpRange.name: me1200QosQceIpv6DscpRange
me1200QosQceIpv6DscpRange.description: The DSCP value to be compared. If the Ipv6DscpOp object in the same row is range(2), this object will be the ending DSCP value of the range. Valid range is 0-63. This object can only be configured if FrameType is ipv6(5) and Ipv6DscpOp is range(2).

me1200QosQceIpv6Protocol.name: me1200QosQceIpv6Protocol
me1200QosQceIpv6Protocol.description: The protocol number field in the IPv6 header used to indicate a higher layer protocol. The packets protocol number field is AND-ed with the value of Ipv6ProtocolMask and then compared with the value of this object. If Ipv46rotocol and Ipv6protocolMask are 0, this entry matches any IPv6 protocol. Valid range is 0-255. This object can only be configured if FrameType is ipv6(5).

me1200QosQceIpv6ProtocolMask.name: me1200QosQceIpv6ProtocolMask
me1200QosQceIpv6ProtocolMask.description: The specified IPv6 protocol number mask. Valid values are 0 or 255. This object can only be configured if FrameType is ipv6(5).

me1200QosQceIpv6SrcIp.name: me1200QosQceIpv6SrcIp
me1200QosQceIpv6SrcIp.description: The specified IPv6 source address. The packets source address is AND-ed with the value of Ipv6SrcIpMask and then compared with the value of this object. If Ipv6SrcIP and Ipv6SrcIpMask are all zeros, this entry matches any IPv6 source address. Only the least significant 32 bits of this object are used. This object can only be configured if FrameType is ipv6(5).

me1200QosQceIpv6SrcIpMask.name: me1200QosQceIpv6SrcIpMask
me1200QosQceIpv6SrcIpMask.description: The specified IPv6 source address mask. Only the least significant 32 bits of this object are used. This object can only be configured if FrameType is ipv6(5).

me1200QosQceIpv6DestIp.name: me1200QosQceIpv6DestIp
me1200QosQceIpv6DestIp.description: The specified IPv6 destination address. The packets destination address is AND-ed with the value of Ipv6DestIpMask and then compared with the value of this object. If Ipv6DestIP and Ipv6DestIpMask are all zeros, this entry matches any IPv6 destination address. Only the least significant 32 bits of this object are used. This object can only be configured if FrameType is ipv6(5).

me1200QosQceIpv6DestIpMask.name: me1200QosQceIpv6DestIpMask
me1200QosQceIpv6DestIpMask.description: The specified IPv6 destination address mask. Only the least significant 32 bits of this object are used. This object can only be configured if FrameType is ipv6(5).

me1200QosQceIpv6SrcPortOp.name: me1200QosQceIpv6SrcPortOp
me1200QosQceIpv6SrcPortOp.description: Indicates how a packet's source TCP/UDP port number is to be compared. This object can only be configured if FrameType is ipv6(5).

me1200QosQceIpv6SrcPort.name: me1200QosQceIpv6SrcPort
me1200QosQceIpv6SrcPort.description: The source port number of the TCP or UDP protocol. If the Ipv6SrcPortOp object in the same row is range(2), this object will be the starting port number of the port range. Valid range is 0-65535. This object can only be configured if FrameType is ipv6(5) and Ipv6SrcPortOp is not any(0).

me1200QosQceIpv6SrcPortRange.name: me1200QosQceIpv6SrcPortRange
me1200QosQceIpv6SrcPortRange.description: The source port number of the TCP or UDP protocol. If the Ipv6SrcPortOp object in the same row is range(2), this object will be the ending port number of the port range. Valid range is 0-65535. This object can only be configured if FrameType is ipv6(5) and Ipv6SrcPortOp is range(2).

me1200QosQceIpv6DestPortOp.name: me1200QosQceIpv6DestPortOp
me1200QosQceIpv6DestPortOp.description: Indicates how a packet's destination TCP/UDP port number is to be compared. This object can only be configured if FrameType is ipv6(5).

me1200QosQceIpv6DestPort.name: me1200QosQceIpv6DestPort
me1200QosQceIpv6DestPort.description: The destination port number of the TCP or UDP protocol. If the Ipv6DestPortOp object in the same row is range(2), this object will be the starting port number of the port range. Valid range is 0-65535. This object can only be configured if FrameType is ipv6(5) and Ipv6DestPortOp is not any(0).

me1200QosQceIpv6DestPortRange.name: me1200QosQceIpv6DestPortRange
me1200QosQceIpv6DestPortRange.description: The source port number of the TCP or UDP protocol. If the Ipv6DestPortOp object in the same row is range(2), this object will be the ending port number of the port range. Valid range is 0-65535. This object can only be configured if FrameType is ipv6(5) and Ipv6DestPortOp is range(2).

me1200QosQceActionCosEnable.name: me1200QosQceActionCosEnable
me1200QosQceActionCosEnable.description: If true, the packet is classified to the CoS value in ActionCos.

me1200QosQceActionCos.name: me1200QosQceActionCos
me1200QosQceActionCos.description: The CoS value used for classification. Valid range is 0-7.

me1200QosQceActionDplEnable.name: me1200QosQceActionDplEnable
me1200QosQceActionDplEnable.description: If true, the packet is classified to the DPL value in ActionDpl.

me1200QosQceActionDpl.name: me1200QosQceActionDpl
me1200QosQceActionDpl.description: The DPL value used for classification. Valid range is 0-1.

me1200QosQceActionDscpEnable.name: me1200QosQceActionDscpEnable
me1200QosQceActionDscpEnable.description: If true, the packet is classified to the DSCP value in ActionDscp.

me1200QosQceActionDscp.name: me1200QosQceActionDscp
me1200QosQceActionDscp.description: The DSCP value used for classification. Valid range is 0-1.

me1200QosQceActionPcpDeiEnable.name: me1200QosQceActionPcpDeiEnable
me1200QosQceActionPcpDeiEnable.description: If true, the packet is classified to the PCP value in ActionPcp and the DEI value in ActionDei.

me1200QosQceActionPcp.name: me1200QosQceActionPcp
me1200QosQceActionPcp.description: The PCP value used for classification. Valid range is 0-7.

me1200QosQceActionDei.name: me1200QosQceActionDei
me1200QosQceActionDei.description: The DEI value used for classification. Valid range is 0-1.

me1200QosIfConfigDscpClassify.description: Selects if and how the classified DSCP is based on the classified CoS and DPL for IPv4 and IPv6 packets on ingress. If a packet is selected for being classified to a new DSCP, the classification in based on the classified CoS mapped to a new DSCP value through the qosCosToDscpTable. If the classified DPL is 1, the new DSCP value is taken from the DscpDp1 entry, otherwise it is taken from the Dscp entry. Valid values are: 'none' : Always classify to the DSCP value in the received packet and ignore the classified CoS and DPL. 'zero' : If the DSCP value in the received packet is 0, then classify to a new DSCP value based on the classified CoS and DPL. 'selected' : If the DSCP value in the received packet is enabled in qosDscpTable.Classify, then classify to a new DSCP value based on the classified CoS and DPL. 'all' : Always classify to a new DSCP value based on the classified CoS and DPL.

me1200QosIfConfigDscpRemark.name: me1200QosIfConfigDscpRemark

'rewrite' : Write the classified DSCP into the packet. 'remap' : Remap the classified DSCP through qosDscpTable, and write the value from EgressTranslation into the packet. 'remap-dp' : Remap the classified DSCP through qosDscpTable. If the classified DPL is 0 then write the value from EgressTranslation into the packet, otherwise write the value from EgressTranslationDp1 into the packet.
